<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="110" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace longer than wide; regions on dorsal surface well defined with gastric, cardiac, intestinal and branchial regions markedly elevated; cardiac region with paired rounded prominences; branchial regions each with 1 conspicuous tubercle on posterior part; external orbital tooth directed anteriorly, subacutely pointed, 2 blunt lateral teeth posterior to external orbital tooth; no lateral constrictions. Front broad, markedly bilobed, not constricted at base. Postfrontal ridges absent. Orbit large; upper orbital margin nearly transverse, markedly sinuous; lower orbital margin bordered with minute granules, inner orbital tooth small, blunt; 1 small but conspicuous subconical tubercle just below inner orbital tooth. Ocular peduncle constricted; cornea large, just reaching external orbital tooth. Antennules folded slightly obliquely; basal article large, but not particularly inflated; inter-antennular septum triangular, narrow in upper part. Antennae in orbital hiatus; flagellum greatly reduced, with long apical filamentous seta. Central region of epistome convex, supported by short median ridge in buccal cavity. Maxillipeds 3 fully closing buccal cavity; lateral margin of merus somewhat expanded, noticeably convex; carpus inserted medially on distal margin of merus; exopodal flagellum well developed. Male cheliped moderately stout; merus slightly narrowing distally, without subdistal spine on upper margin; carpus without prominent tooth or spine on inner surface; occlusal margins of fingers each with row of small teeth; tips of fingers pointed, crossing distally. Ambulatory legs moderately slender; meri each without subdistal spine on anterior margin; propodi unarmed at flexor distal angles. Male pleon gradually narrowing toward telson; somites 4–6 functionally fused though sutures demarcating somites 4/5 and 5/6 on external surface still discernible (while no suture delimited on internal surface); somite 6 with low convexity on lateral margins proximally. Male gonopod 1 relatively slender, not recurved, gradually tapering distally. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,830,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Remarks.</emphasis>
As mentioned above, the new taxon superficially resembles species of the camptrandriid genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tan &amp; Ng" authorityYear="1999" box="[151,238,867,890]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Moguai" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,238,867,890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Moguai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2014" box="[291,431,867,890]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Paramoguai" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[291,431,867,890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Paramoguai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the nearly straight, non-recurved gonopod 1 clearly excludes it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[1250,1433,866,891]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camptandriidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai &amp; Fujita, 2018" authorityName="Komai &amp; Fujita" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,372,903,926]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Mirograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper" status="n. gen., n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[151,372,903,926]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Mirograpsus asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[388,570,902,927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[388,570,902,927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" rank="species">n. gen., n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[879,1106,903,926]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[879,1106,903,926]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Apograpsus paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the sole representative of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Komai &amp; Wada" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,285,938,961]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,285,938,961]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Apograpsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in the general structure of the carapace, which is longer than wide with markedly elevated gastric, cardiac and intestinal regions, with the cardiac region possessing paired rounded prominences. The following major differences between the two genera, however, warrant the establishment of the new genus (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
for character states of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Komai &amp; Wada" authorityYear="2008" box="[541,675,1046,1069]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[541,675,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Apograpsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): (1) the carapace is devoid of postfrontal ridges (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1339,1045,1070]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[223,1350,237,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607). A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, posterior part of carapace dorsal surface, posterior view; C, frontal part of carapace, left eye, antennules, left antenna and epistome, anterior view; D, lower orbital margin and suborbital region, ventral view (setae omitted); E, left maxilliped 3, outer view; F, thoracic sternum and gonopods 1, ventral view; G, pleon, outer view; H, left gonopod 1 and penis, ventral view; I, left gonopod 1, dorsal view; J, right gonopod 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) (versus longitudinal postfrontal ridges are present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[656,765,1081,1105]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[656,765,1081,1105]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[816,1059,1081,1106]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17A); (2) the lateral margins of the carapace are devoid of constriction posterior to the external orbital teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1217,1116,1141]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[223,1350,237,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607). A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, posterior part of carapace dorsal surface, posterior view; C, frontal part of carapace, left eye, antennules, left antenna and epistome, anterior view; D, lower orbital margin and suborbital region, ventral view (setae omitted); E, left maxilliped 3, outer view; F, thoracic sternum and gonopods 1, ventral view; G, pleon, outer view; H, left gonopod 1 and penis, ventral view; I, left gonopod 1, dorsal view; J, right gonopod 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) (versus distinctly constricted posterior to the external orbital teeth in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[727,836,1153,1176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[727,836,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[887,1130,1152,1177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17A); (3) the antennal flagellum is greatly reduced, bearing a long filamentous terminal seta (
<figureCitation box="[942,1028,1188,1213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[223,1350,237,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607). A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, posterior part of carapace dorsal surface, posterior view; C, frontal part of carapace, left eye, antennules, left antenna and epistome, anterior view; D, lower orbital margin and suborbital region, ventral view (setae omitted); E, left maxilliped 3, outer view; F, thoracic sternum and gonopods 1, ventral view; G, pleon, outer view; H, left gonopod 1 and penis, ventral view; I, left gonopod 1, dorsal view; J, right gonopod 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) (versus multi-articulated, without a prominent terminal seta in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[455,565,1224,1248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[455,565,1224,1248]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[617,861,1223,1248]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17A, B); (4) the male chela is large and stout, with the fingers pointed and crossing when closed (
<figureCitation box="[726,845,1259,1284]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1951,1973]" captionTargetBox="[211,1388,277,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,240,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607), left pereopods. A, cheliped, dorsal view; B, same, chela, outer view; C, pereopod 2, dorsal view; D, pereopod 3, dorsal view; E, pereopod 4, dorsal view; F, pereopod 5, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614424/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
) (versus small and slender, tips of fingers are spoonshaped, being similar to the female chela in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[684,798,1296,1319]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[684,798,1296,1319]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[859,1116,1295,1320]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17G); (5) the meri of pereopods 2–5 are unarmed on the anterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[742,808,1331,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1951,1973]" captionTargetBox="[211,1388,277,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,240,1894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607), left pereopods. A, cheliped, dorsal view; B, same, chela, outer view; C, pereopod 2, dorsal view; D, pereopod 3, dorsal view; E, pereopod 4, dorsal view; F, pereopod 5, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614424/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C–F) (versus each armed with a small subterminal spine in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[179,287,1367,1391]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[179,287,1367,1391]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[336,577,1366,1391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17H, I); and (6) the male pleomeres 4–6 are functionally fused (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1428,1366,1391]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[223,1350,237,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607). A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, posterior part of carapace dorsal surface, posterior view; C, frontal part of carapace, left eye, antennules, left antenna and epistome, anterior view; D, lower orbital margin and suborbital region, ventral view (setae omitted); E, left maxilliped 3, outer view; F, thoracic sternum and gonopods 1, ventral view; G, pleon, outer view; H, left gonopod 1 and penis, ventral view; I, left gonopod 1, dorsal view; J, right gonopod 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
) (versus all freely articulated in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[507,616,1403,1426]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[507,616,1403,1426]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[670,916,1402,1427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17D). Other notable differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Komai &amp; Fujita" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,252,1439,1462]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Mirograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper">
<emphasis box="[151,252,1439,1462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">M. asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[261,416,1438,1463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">n. gen, n. sp.</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[474,585,1439,1462]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[474,585,1439,1462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: the front lacks long setae on each anterolateral part (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1338,1438,1463]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[223,1350,237,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607). A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, posterior part of carapace dorsal surface, posterior view; C, frontal part of carapace, left eye, antennules, left antenna and epistome, anterior view; D, lower orbital margin and suborbital region, ventral view (setae omitted); E, left maxilliped 3, outer view; F, thoracic sternum and gonopods 1, ventral view; G, pleon, outer view; H, left gonopod 1 and penis, ventral view; I, left gonopod 1, dorsal view; J, right gonopod 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) (versus with a few long setae are present at each anterolateral part of the front in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[980,1090,1474,1498]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[980,1090,1474,1498]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[1142,1386,1474,1499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17A, B); the branchial region of the carapace has one conspicuous tubercle in 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai &amp; Fujita, 2018" authorityName="Komai &amp; Fujita" authorityYear="2018" box="[1051,1152,1511,1534]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Mirograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper" status="n. gen., n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1051,1152,1511,1534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">M. asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1161,1322,1510,1535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1161,1322,1510,1535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" rank="species">n. gen., n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1340,1428,1510,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[223,1350,237,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607). A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, posterior part of carapace dorsal surface, posterior view; C, frontal part of carapace, left eye, antennules, left antenna and epistome, anterior view; D, lower orbital margin and suborbital region, ventral view (setae omitted); E, left maxilliped 3, outer view; F, thoracic sternum and gonopods 1, ventral view; G, pleon, outer view; H, left gonopod 1 and penis, ventral view; I, left gonopod 1, dorsal view; J, right gonopod 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) (versus tubercle absent in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[454,566,1546,1569]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[454,566,1546,1569]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[621,871,1545,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17A); and the male pleomere 6 bears a low convexity on the proximal part of each lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[790,880,1581,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[223,1350,237,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[196,1392,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mirograpsus asper n. gen, n. sp., holotype, male (5.8×5.1 mm; CBM-ZC 14607). A, carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, posterior part of carapace dorsal surface, posterior view; C, frontal part of carapace, left eye, antennules, left antenna and epistome, anterior view; D, lower orbital margin and suborbital region, ventral view (setae omitted); E, left maxilliped 3, outer view; F, thoracic sternum and gonopods 1, ventral view; G, pleon, outer view; H, left gonopod 1 and penis, ventral view; I, left gonopod 1, dorsal view; J, right gonopod 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
) (versus no convexity is present on each lateral margin in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Naruse &amp; Kishino" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[265,374,1617,1641]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Apograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paantu">
<emphasis box="[265,374,1617,1641]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">A. paantu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[424,667,1617,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnard" authorityYear="1955" box="[199,331,1653,1677]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Ilyograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,331,1653,1677]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Ilyograpsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, another representative of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stevcic" authorityYear="2005" box="[663,818,1652,1677]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ilyograpsinae">Ilyograpsinae</taxonomicName>
, is readily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Komai &amp; Fujita" authorityYear="2018" box="[1199,1343,1653,1676]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Mirograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1343,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Mirograpsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the carapace being wider than long, the carapace regions being less defined, meri of the ambulatory legs each armed with a subdistal spine on the anterior margin, and the feely articulated pleomeres 4–6 (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K." box="[1147,1388,1724,1749]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="357 - 384" refId="ref3775" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Wada, K. (2008) A revision of the estuarine crab genus Ilyograpsus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with descriptions of a new genus and one new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 56, 357 - 384." type="journal article" year="2008">Komai &amp; Wada 2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 10).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
The family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1851" box="[356,568,1795,1820]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Macrophthalmidae</taxonomicName>
is now represented by 10 genera classified into three subfamilies, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1851" box="[151,366,1831,1856]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Macrophthalminae">Macrophthalminae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stevcic" authorityYear="2005" box="[377,529,1831,1856]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ilyograpsinae">Ilyograpsinae</taxonomicName>
and Tritodynaminae (
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F." box="[779,946,1831,1856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref3939" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F. (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 17 (Supplement), 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[822,872,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnes, R. S. K." box="[958,1103,1832,1856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="31 - 49" refId="ref3597" refString="Barnes, R. S. K. (2010) A review of the sentinel &amp; allied crabs (Crustacea: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with particular reference to the genus Macrophthalmus. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 58, 31 - 49." type="journal article" year="2010">Barnes 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Davie, P. J. F." box="[1115,1249,1831,1856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="815 - 827" refId="ref3674" refString="Davie, P. J. F. (2009) A new genus and species of Macrophthalmidae (Crustacea: Brachyura: Ocypodoidea) from the Northern Territory, Australia. Crustaceana, 82, 815 - 827. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854009 X 427360" type="journal article" year="2009">Davie 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Davie, P. J. F." box="[1260,1319,1832,1856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="149 - 219" refId="ref3726" refString="Davie, P. J. F. (2012) A review of Macrophthalmus sensu lato (Crustacea: Decapoda: Macrophthalmidae) from Australia, including two new species and new records. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, Nature, 56, 149 - 219." type="journal article" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R." pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="2835 - 2848" refId="ref3827" refString="Naderloo, R. (2013) The sentinel crabs of the genus Chaenostoma Stimpson, 1858 (Crustacea: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae), with description of a new species and new records. Journal of Natural History, 47, 2835 - 2848. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2013.807948" type="journal article" year="2013">Naderloo 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker, A. &amp; Ng, P. K. L." box="[225,443,1867,1892]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="369 - 376" refId="ref3534" refString="Anker, A. &amp; Ng, P. K. L. (2014) Tritodynamia serratipes sp. nov., a new marine crab from Singapore (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae). Zootaxa, 3826 (3), 369 - 376 http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3826.2.6" type="journal article" year="2014">Anker &amp; Ng 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Teng, S. - J. &amp; Shih, H. - T. &amp; Naderloo, R. &amp; Corbari, L." box="[458,655,1867,1892]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" pagination="15 - 27" refId="ref4048" refString="Teng, S. - J., Shih, H. - T., Naderloo, R. &amp; Corbari, L. (2016) A review of the Chaenostoma boscii species-complex (Decapoda: Brachyura: Macrophthalmidae) from the Indo-West Pacific. Crustacean Research, 45, 15 - 27. https: // doi. org / 10.18353 / crustacea. 45.0 _ 15" type="journal article" year="2016">
Teng 
<emphasis box="[524,576,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
), but in all of the known genera, the male pleon consists of freely articulated somites 1–6 + telson. In this regard, consequently, 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai &amp; Fujita, 2018" authorityName="Komai &amp; Fujita" authorityYear="2018" box="[844,987,1904,1927]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Mirograpsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[844,987,1904,1927]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Mirograpsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[995,1074,1902,1927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[995,1074,1902,1927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unique in the family.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="110" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1938,1963]" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is an arbitrary combination of the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[988,1052,1939,1962]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">mirus</emphasis>
”, meaning amazing or marvelous, and the generic name “ 
<emphasis box="[418,513,1975,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="110">Grapsus</emphasis>
”, which is a common suffix for the genera of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stevcic" authorityYear="2005" box="[1217,1373,1974,1999]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ilyograpsinae">Ilyograpsinae</taxonomicName>
. This name alludes to the unusual appearance of this crab among the macrophthalmids. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
